Text: JS stands for JavaScript, which is a high-level, dynamic, and interpreted programming language that conforms to the ECMAScript specification. JavaScript is widely used in web development to create interactive effects within web browsers, as part of both the client-side and server-side scripting. It enables developers to build dynamic content, control multimedia, animate images, and much more, essentially making web pages more interactive and user-friendly. JavaScript should not be confused with Java, as they are distinct languages with different uses, syntax, and capabilities.
